Q.1 <!DOCTYPE html> is it a tag of html? If not, what is it and why do we use it?

Ans = <!DOCTYPE html> declaration is not an HTML tag. It is an instruction to the web browser about what version
of HTML the page is written in. This ensures that the web page is parsed the same way by different web browsers.
It is called as the document type declaration (DTD).

Q.2 Explain Semantic tags in html? And why do we need it?

Ans = Semantic tags help the search engines and other user devices to determine the importance and context of web
pages. The pages made with semantic elements are much easier to read. It has greater accessibility. It offers a 
better user experience. It makes the HTML more comprehensible by better defining the different sections and layout 
of web pages.

Q.3 Differentiate between HTML Tags and Elements?

Ans = HTML tags usually exist in pairs consisting of a starting and an ending tag. However, some tags do not have a 
closing tag. 
HTML Elements contain a starting tag, content, and an ending tag. If there is no content in an HTML Element, it is
called an Empty HTML Element.

Q.6 What are some of the advantages of HTML5 over its previous versions?

Ans = some of the advantages of HTML5 are
      -> MUltimedia support
      -> Short and simple syntax
      -> Improved security features
      -> Include semantic tags
      -> Cross-platform support

Q.8 What is the difference between <figure> tag and <img> tag?

Ans = The figure tag is used to semantically organize the content of images, videos, audios or even charts or tables,
block of codes in the HTML document.
<figure> tag is a container tag. 
This tag provides a container for content that is equivalent to a figure.
The image tag is used to add an image to an HTML page. <img> tag can only insert image.
<img> tag is a void tag.
The HTML <img> tag is used for embedding images into an HTML document.

Q.9 Whatâ€™s the difference between html tag and attribute  and give example of some global attributes?

Ans = A tag is a way of representing an HTML element in the program . 
HTML tags are used to hold the HTML element. HTML element holds the content.
HTML tags are almost like keywords where every single tag has unique meaning.

Attribute:
An attribute is a way of describing the characteristics of an HTML element.
HTML attributes specify various additional properties to the existing HTML element.
Give example of some global attributes:
-> id : It is a unique identifier that is used to specify the document and used by CSS and JavaScript to perform
a certain task for a unique element.
-> lang : It is used to specify the language of the element content.
-> style : It describe how a document will be presented in a browser.
-> title : It is used to define the title of an HTML document, sets the title in the browser toolbar, and provides
the title for the web page when it is added to favorites.
